bcl:definition.bcl:text:
avoidable reversal event means a reversal event that occurred because the project
proponent, by failing to comply with the maintenance requirements,
substantially increased the risk that the reversal event would occur;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
in relation to a monitoring report, baseline emissions for the monitoring
                  report period minus project emissions described in paragraph (c) of the
                  definition of "project emissions";

in relation to a monitoring report, the amount of greenhouse gas emissions,
                  determined in accordance with the project plan, that occurred from all
                  selected sources in the monitoring report period;

in relation to a monitoring report, the amount of greenhouse gas emissions,
                  determined in accordance with the project plan, that was removed by all
                  selected sinks in the monitoring report period;

in relation to a monitoring report, project removals described in
                  paragraph (c) of the definition of "project removals" minus baseline
                  removals for the monitoring report period;

in respect of subsection (7), the combined total of the emissions reduction
                and the removals enhancement for the monitoring report period is greater
                than zero;

bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
the total amount of the emissions reduction and the removals
                  enhancement for all project report periods prior to the project report
                  period to which the project report relates;

the amount of any impaired project reduction during the monitoring
                  report period and the numbers that were used to calculate that
                  amount;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
if the project is a sequestration project, an assertion that the measurements
                and calculations that resulted in the amounts asserted under paragraph (e)
                were carried out in accordance with the applicable protocol;
